<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:id="@+id/main"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    tools:context=".safetytip.OversharingSocialMediaActivity"
    android:orientation="vertical"
    android:layout_margin="10dp">

    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="Avoid oversharing social media"
        android:layout_marginStart="10dp"
        android:layout_marginTop="15dp"
        android:textStyle="bold"
        android:textColor="@color/black"
        android:drawableEnd="@drawable/socialmediaoversharing"
        android:textSize="31sp"/>

    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="Avoiding oversharing on social media is crucial for maintaining your privacy and safety. Here’s a detailed breakdown of how to protect yourself:"
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="1:  Avoid sharing sensitive information such as your full address, phone number, or personal ID numbers."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="2:  Avoid posting your exact location or geotagging your photos in real-time, especially if you are somewhere isolated or in a high-risk area. Criminals can use your location to track your movements or know when you’re not home."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="- Example: Instead of saying, At home all day, try saying something vague like, (Enjoying a quiet day off). Similarly, wait to post location-specific photos after you’ve left the place. "
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="3dp"/>
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="3:  Posting that you’re going on vacation or a business trip can leave your home vulnerable to break-ins. Criminals may be watching your posts, and by sharing this information, you could inadvertently alert them that your house is empty."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="4:  To avoid advertising that your home is unoccupied, wait until after you've returned to share travel photos or updates. This helps prevent criminals from taking advantage of your absence."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="5:  Make sure you understand the privacy settings on each social media platform and adjust them to control who can see your posts. For example, you can make your Facebook profile private, limiting access to friends only, or create custom lists for different groups of people (family, work colleagues, etc.)."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"/>
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="6:  On platforms like Instagram or Twitter, you can choose whether to share posts with the public, a select group, or just friends. It's important to set these preferences to limit exposure."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="7:  Be cautious about allowing others to tag you in posts or photos. If someone tags you in an embarrassing or compromising situation, it could damage your reputation or expose private information."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"/>
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="8:  What's the Risk? Before posting something, think about how it might affect your safety or reputation. Will it compromise your privacy? Could someone use this information maliciously? Avoid posting any content that you wouldn’t want to be available to the public."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="9:  Avoid posting overly personal details, like conflicts, relationship issues, financial troubles, or health problems. These are best discussed privately and may leave you vulnerable to exploitation or manipulation."
        android:textSize="24sp" />
    android:layout_margin="10dp"
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="10:  If you have children, be mindful of sharing too many details about their lives. Posting about their location, school, or extracurricular activities can expose them to risks, like kidnapping or bullying."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="11:  Many platforms have age restrictions (e.g., users must be 13 or older) to protect minors. Avoid sharing images, names, or private details about children if they don’t have their own social media accounts."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"/>
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="12:  Be cautious when discussing your work environment, colleagues, or job-related problems online. Oversharing about your workplace can not only cause conflicts with your employer but also make you a target for scams or phishing attacks (e.g., cybercriminals impersonating colleagues or managers)."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="13: Never share confidential work details or personal information about clients, customers, or colleagues. Doing so could lead to legal consequences, loss of trust, or data breaches."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />

    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="14:  It’s natural to feel the urge to vent online, but oversharing personal frustrations or vulnerabilities can make you an easy target for scammers or online predators. If you’re upset, take time to process your emotions privately rather than airing them online."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="15:  Posting personal vulnerabilities might invite unwanted attention or even cyberbullying. Negative comments or judgment from strangers can affect your emotional well-being."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="16:  Avoid oversharing strong political, religious, or social opinions unless you are sure of the audience you are addressing. While it’s okay to express your views, doing so on a public platform can open you up to online harassment, arguments, or even backlash."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="17:  Keep in mind that people have diverse opinions, and what you share online can be seen by anyone, potentially leading to misunderstandings or conflict."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="18:  Scammers often try to manipulate people into sharing personal information through links disguised as genuine offers or messages. If you receive a suspicious message on social media, do not click any links, and report the user to the platform."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="19:  Scammers may use social media to try and trick you into sharing sensitive information (such as passwords, social security numbers, or banking details). Be cautious of unsolicited messages or friend requests from people you don’t know."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="20:  Regularly check your privacy settings on social media platforms. These settings may change after platform updates, so keeping them updated ensures your information is protected."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="21: What you post today can stay on the internet for years, even if you delete it. Be mindful of what you share, as future employers, colleges, or others may find your social media history."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />

    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="22:  Every so often, Google your name to see what comes up. This helps you understand what personal information is publicly accessible and gives you the opportunity to remove or edit anything you no longer wish to share."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="23: Many people enjoy checking into places like restaurants, gyms, or other public spots. While this can be fun, it’s important to consider whether it’s a good idea to share your exact location, especially when it’s somewhere you visit frequently."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="24: Be selective about who you accept as a friend or follower on social media. Don’t accept requests from people you don’t know or trust. Scammers and malicious users often create fake profiles to gain access to personal information."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="25: Periodically review your friend and follower lists to ensure only trusted individuals have access to your posts. Remove anyone who no longer needs to be connected to you or whose behavior feels suspicious."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="  - Enable Two-Factor Authentication: Many social media platforms offer two-factor authentication, which adds an extra layer of security to your account. It typically involves receiving a code via SMS or an authentication app when logging in from a new device."
        android:textSize="24sp"
        android:layout_margin="10dp"
        />

</LinearLayout>